>
>[Thoughts]
>I'm assuming that when the power went out the clock stopped at 3:30 
>and the time on the watch was 6:45. So the power must have gone out 
>at 3:30. But then this can't be right

Hi,

Thanks for writing to Dr. Math.

Usually when the power goes out, the clock resets to midnight. Many
clocks will then proceed to keep time but blink so you will know that
there has been an interruption in power.

Does this help?  Please feel free to write back with any questions you
may have.

